    },
    {
      "id": "9adffdf1_6378af2b",
      "file_path": "docker-compose.yml",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 13,
      "message": "Maybe it's just me, but when using docker-compose from command line in form \"docker-compose up <service-name>\" it was more convenient to use short name \"kafka\" :)  I don't mind the change, but we could think of using shortnames for declaring components and long-names in `network:aliases` section",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3701,
        "name": "Filip Krzywka",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "filip.krzywka@nokia.com",
        "username": "fkrzywka"
      },
      "updated": "2018-12-10 11:42:58.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "9adffdf1_437d6b1b",
      "file_path": "docker-compose.yml",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 42,
      "message": "docker.io/consul:1.0.6?\n\nAs another approach we could use something small like `alpine` image and use `curl` - this would follow our actual deployment on DCAE platform.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3701,
        "name": "Filip Krzywka",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "filip.krzywka@nokia.com",
        "username": "fkrzywka"
      },
      "updated": "2018-12-10 11:42:58.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
