    {
      "id": "9adffdf1_83ffd366",
      "file_path": "sources/hv-collector-core/src/main/kotlin/org/onap/dcae/collectors/veshv/impl/socket/NettyTcpServer.kt",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 112,
      "message": "Please take a look at the definition. warn gets message provider. It's a shortcut to withWarn {log(\"msg\")}, as it's most used feature. withWarn moves us to the AtLevelLogger context (this binding). Unfortunately I cannot use the same name because the compiler fails with error.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2683,
        "name": "Piotr Jaszczyk",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "piotr.jaszczyk@nokia.com",
        "username": "jaszczur"
      },
      "updated": "2018-12-10 13:23:11.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9adffdf1_a39d375b",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "9adffdf1_23ee27b5",
      "file_path": "sources/hv-collector-core/src/main/kotlin/org/onap/dcae/collectors/veshv/impl/wire/WireChunkDecoder.kt",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 57,
      "message": "Please note that ClientContext is defined in core module and handleReact... in utils. We could however provide an adaptation layer as in case of other loggers.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2683,
        "name": "Piotr Jaszczyk",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "piotr.jaszczyk@nokia.com",
        "username": "jaszczur"
      },
      "updated": "2018-12-10 13:23:11.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9adffdf1_e3ba5fbf",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "9adffdf1_633bcf38",
      "file_path": "sources/hv-collector-core/src/main/kotlin/org/onap/dcae/collectors/veshv/model/ClientContext.kt",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 36,
      "message": "In case of logging it would be fine, but if we wanted to actually use these values then the client code will get more complicated (handling all different combinations of absence). That said, arrow monad comprehensions can help here. I think we can use a here internally + empty constructor. Just let's not use a Map<Mdckey,Option> directly in cleint code.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2683,
        "name": "Piotr Jaszczyk",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "piotr.jaszczyk@nokia.com",
        "username": "jaszczur"
      },
      "updated": "2018-12-10 13:23:11.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9adffdf1_83b113e3",
      "unresolved": false
    },
